To create a systemd service file for a secure Python Flask application, follow these steps and create the following files:

1. Create a user for the application:

```bash
sudo useradd --system --no-create-home --shell /usr/bin/nologin appuser
```

2. Change the ownership of the application directory and file to the newly created user:

```bash
sudo chown appuser:appuser /opt/app/app.py
sudo chown -R appuser:appuser /opt/app/
```

3. Create a new group for the application:

```bash
sudo groupadd appgroup
```

4. Change the group ownership of the application directory and file to the new group:

```bash
sudo chgrp -R appgroup /opt/app/
```

